com.solacesystems.jcsmp

Class JCSMPErrorResponseSubcodeEx

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.solacesystems.jcsmp.JCSMPErrorResponseSubcodeEx

  • public final class JCSMPErrorResponseSubcodeEx
extends Object
    Subcode that gives more detailed information about an error response. This class replaces the deprecated JCSMPErrorResponseSubcode.

    General Login Exception Subcodes

    The following subcodes can apply to error response exceptions resulting from failed login attempts. As a login attempt can result from every session operation that communicates with the appliance, they are listed here to avoid repetition.
    • JCSMPErrorResponseSubcodeEx.CLIENT_NAME_INVALID
    • JCSMPErrorResponseSubcodeEx.CLIENT_NAME_ALREADY_IN_USE
    • JCSMPErrorResponseSubcodeEx.LOGIN_FAILURE
    • JCSMPErrorResponseSubcodeEx.CLIENT_USERNAME_IS_SHUTDOWN
    • JCSMPErrorResponseSubcodeEx.DYNAMIC_CLIENTS_NOT_ALLOWED
    • JCSMPErrorResponseSubcodeEx.CLIENT_ACL_DENIED
    • JCSMPErrorResponseSubcodeEx.INVALID_VIRTUAL_ADDRESS
    • JCSMPErrorResponseSubcodeEx.MSG_VPN_NOT_ALLOWED
    • JCSMPErrorResponseSubcodeEx.MSG_VPN_UNAVAILABLE
    • JCSMPErrorResponseSubcodeEx.CLIENT_DELETE_IN_PROGRESS
    • JCSMPErrorResponseSubcodeEx.TOO_MANY_CLIENTS
